properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Warm and humid conditions expected Monday afternoon and evening. A warm and humid air mass is expected to move into portions of northwestern Ontario near the Minnesota border Monday afternoon. Afternoon highs in the upper twenties will combine with the humidity to create humidex values in the mid thirties. Temperatures on Tuesday should be a few degrees cooler with lesser humidity. These conditions pose a health risk when you are not used to the heat. Everyone is at risk from heat, especially older adults, infants and young children, and people with chronic illnesses. You are advised to 1) drink plenty of cool liquids before feeling thirsty; and 2) keep cool by dressing for the weather and spending a few hours each day in a cool place. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant rainfall for the Kootenays today. A band of thunderstorms moved up from Washington State through the southern Interior last night, producing extensive lightning, gusty winds and 5 to 20 mm of rainfall. Another disturbance will move into B.C. from Washington this morning, producing more rainfall today over the Kootenays and Columbias. Additional rainfall amounts of 10 to 25 mm are forecast for today, with up to 35 mm where rainfall is enhanced by morning thunderstorms. Potential impacts from thunderstorms and widespread rainfall include: rising rivers, downed trees, flash flooding, and danger to those recreating or working outside. Environment and Climate Change Canada meteorologists will continue to monitor the situation. Description: At 5:32 p.m. MDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a line of severe thunderstorms capable of producing very strong wind gusts, up to nickel size hail and heavy rain. The line of thunderstorms is located from Acme to Elnora and is moving north at 10 km/h. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Remember, severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of dangerous thunderstorms that may be capable of producing damaging wind gusts and damaging hail. A developing low pressure system over Alberta is introducing favourable conditions for the development of thunderstorms in central Saskatchewan late this afternoon and evening. It is expected that storms may be isolated initially, and some may become severe with threats of hail and wind. As time progresses, these storms will coalesce into a larger complex with strong winds being the primary severe weather threat. As this event progresses, it is expected that the watch area will be expanded. ### Very large hail can damage property, break windows, dent vehicles and cause serious injury. Very strong wind gusts can damage buildings, down trees and blow large vehicles off the road. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: A long episode of rain, at times heavy, is expected. Total rainfall: up to 70 mm. Locations: Burgeo - Ramea. Time span: until Tuesday afternoon. Rainfall warnings are issued when significant rainfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of severe thunderstorms that may be capable of producing strong wind gusts, large hail and heavy rain. Some of these thunderstorms may become severe in nature. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Remember, severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.
